    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Config migration (eslintrc ‚Üí flat config) + dependency bump; no .ts/.tsx code modification (lint fixes are excluded from FULL by deliberate scoping). STANDARD per Step 3.5.5 (creates new config file with explicit constraints; lint clean is the test).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>I</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Per spec NFR-06 / plan B-9: migrate `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/` from
    ESLint v8 (`.eslintrc.json`) to v9 (`eslint.config.js` flat config). NOTE: ESLint v9 is
    already in package.json (`"eslint": "^9.17.0"`); investigation shows NO `.eslintrc.json`
    currently exists either ‚Äî so this task is likely "create the missing flat config and
    verify lint works" rather than "migrate from v8". Confirm during step 1.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE TypeScript build engineer. Familiar with ESLint v9 flat-config schema
    (https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/configuration-files), typescript-eslint
    v8+ flat-config conventions, and React/Fluent v9 lint plugins. Bias toward the smallest
    config that gives meaningful coverage ‚Äî TypeScript + React-hooks + accessibility, no
    overzealous style rules.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (1) `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/eslint.config.js` (or `.mjs`) exists with
    flat-config schema (default export = array of config objects). (2) Any pre-existing
    `.eslintrc.json` is DELETED (none found currently ‚Äî confirm). (3) `package.json` ESLint
    deps are at v9-compatible versions (`@typescript-eslint/*` v8+, `eslint-plugin-react`
    v7.35+, etc.) ‚Äî investigate `--legacy-peer-deps` impact. (4) `npm run lint` runs clean
    (0 errors). (5) Lint covers .ts + .tsx; ignores node_modules, dist, build outputs. NFR-06
    acceptance satisfied.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per backlog B-9 + investigation: `package.json` already lists `"eslint": "^9.17.0"` but
      no `.eslintrc.json` or `eslint.config.js` exists. The lint script
      (`"lint": "eslint src --ext .ts,.tsx"`) uses the legacy `--ext` flag (deprecated in v9
      flat config). So either (a) lint was silently broken / no-config, or (b) there's a
      parent config being inherited. The migration task is: create a minimal but useful
      flat config, ensure deps are aligned, update the lint script if needed, run clean.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/package.json</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/eslint.config.js</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/tsconfig.json</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Flat config MUST be standalone (no inheritance from a non-existent v8 `.eslintrc`). Use `defineConfig` from `eslint` or plain array export.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Lint MUST cover `src/**/*.ts` + `src/**/*.tsx`. Excludes: `node_modules`, `dist`, `build`, `coverage`, `examples` (consider).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Rule set MUST include at minimum: `@typescript-eslint/recommended`, `eslint-plugin-react-hooks/recommended`. Optional: `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y` (only if maintainable ‚Äî no auto-fix-only rules that hide real bugs).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">0 lint errors at task completion. Lint warnings are acceptable but should be enumerated in `notes/b9-lint-warnings.md` so they can be triaged in B-11 or later.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If the `lint` script in package.json uses `--ext` (legacy), update to flat-config style: `"lint": "eslint src"` (extensions specified inside config via `files: ['**/*.ts', '**/*.tsx']`).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT modify code to silence lint errors. If errors surface, fix the rule scope (e.g., disable noisy rules for tests/) or carry them as warnings ‚Äî do NOT add `// eslint-disable-line` comments.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 ‚Äî ensure react-hooks plugin recognizes React 19 hooks (`use`, `useFormStatus`, etc. if used).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/package.json</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/tsconfig.json</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/plan.original.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/CLAUDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Audit current state">Inspect `Spaarke.UI.Components/package.json` for all ESLint-adjacent deps + scripts. Check for `.eslintrc*`, `eslint.config.*`, or `eslint:` block in package.json. Verify none exist (the file search returned nothing). Run `npm run lint` to capture the current outcome ‚Äî likely an error like "no config found" or silent no-op.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Pin dep versions">Verify `eslint@^9.17.0` plus `typescript-eslint@^8` (flat-config-aware), `eslint-plugin-react-hooks@^5`, `eslint-plugin-react@^7.35+` (if React rules wanted). If older versions present, bump in `package.json`. Note: ESLint v9 + typescript-eslint v8 require Node 18+; verify CI uses compatible Node.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Author flat config">Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/eslint.config.js`. Structure: ESM import of `typescript-eslint`, plain config object with `files`, `languageOptions` (parser, parserOptions), `plugins`, `rules`. Use `tseslint.config(...)` helper if convenient. Include react-hooks plugin. Ignore patterns for `dist`, `node_modules`, `coverage`, `**/*.spec.*` (or scope test files to a separate config block).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Update lint script">If `package.json` lint script uses `--ext`, change to `"lint": "eslint src"` and `"lint:fix": "eslint src --fix"`. Verify the script runs.</step>
    <step order="5" name="Install + verify">Run `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` (per CLAUDE.md repo conventions ‚Äî no `npm ci`). Run `npm run lint`. Capture output.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Resolve errors">If lint reports errors, prefer (a) tightening the file glob to exclude test/__mocks__ as appropriate, or (b) downgrading specific noisy rules to `warn` for now (record in `notes/b9-lint-warnings.md`). Do NOT mass-disable rules; do NOT add `// eslint-disable` lines.</step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify build downstream">Run `npm run build` on Spaarke.UI.Components ‚Äî confirm package still builds. ESLint changes shouldn't affect build, but cross-checking the toolchain is cheap insurance.</step>
    <step order="8" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip task 065 from üî≤ ‚Üí ‚úÖ completed.</step>
    <step order="9" name="Document deviations">If flat config required unexpected refactor (e.g., test files needed a separate config block, or peer deps required broader package-lock churn), record in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r4/notes/`. Note any carry-over warnings for B-11 or later.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="terminal">npm install (with --legacy-peer-deps), npm run lint, npm run build</tool>
    <tool name="Read">Inspect package.json, tsconfig.json</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create eslint.config.js</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Update package.json scripts + deps</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="config">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/eslint.config.js (new ‚Äî flat config)</output>
