  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the new flat config, When `npm run lint` is run from `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/`, Then it exits 0 with 0 errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the flat config file, When inspected, Then it is a valid ESM (or CJS) config exporting an array (or `tseslint.config(...)` result) with explicit `files`, `languageOptions`, `plugins`, and `rules`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given the dep bump, When `package.json` is inspected, Then ESLint is `^9.x` and typescript-eslint is `^8.x` (or newer).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given no legacy config remains, When grep'd for `.eslintrc`, Then no file exists in the package.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Given task 065 is being executed, When this task completes, Then TASK-INDEX.md shows task 065 as ‚úÖ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Reference: https://eslint.org/docs/latest/use/configure/configuration-files (the canonical
    flat-config guide). typescript-eslint v8 has its own flat-config helpers; prefer the
    helper-based approach over hand-rolling parser config. Per CLAUDE.md repo conventions,
    use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund` (not `npm ci`). If the package
    relies on a workspace-level ESLint setup (root-level `eslint.config.js`), check for it
    in step 1 ‚Äî the migration scope may be smaller than expected.
  </notes>

